          "type" : "orderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Format",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Format",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "“The phrase ‘…’ suggests … “",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Format",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "No need to actually explain the words. Just state the phrase and what it suggests. Remember to identify the connotations",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "behind the points in the question, and make sure that each phrase is connected EVERY one of the points",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Somehow according to Ms Afiah’s example answers, you can actually use figurative language to explain the language used.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "For example, “The phrase ‘nipping at noses and ears’ shows that it felt like the wind was biting at these parts of his",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "face”. “like the wind was biting” is technically a metaphor, so ig we’re allowed to use figurative language in our",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "answers.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Tips",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Tips",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Do not reuse words from ANY of your phrases. If a word you want to use to explain phrase A is a part of phrase B,",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "choose an alternative word.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Do not use the same word to explain different phrases. If you use similar explanations to link back to an overall",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "point, change both the words AND the sentence structure.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
